---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Logo from '../components/Logo.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about the HMD Births Heatmaps project, data sources from the Human Mortality Database and UN Population Division, and the technical implementation."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <h1 class="mb-lg">About This Project</h1>

  <section class="p-lg bg-card-bg border border-card-border rounded-lg mb-xl">
    <h2 class="mb-md">Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This project visualizes birth seasonality patterns across countries using data from
      the Human Mortality Database and UN Population Division. The interactive heatmaps
      show how birth rates vary by month across different years.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="p-lg bg-card-bg border border-card-border rounded-lg mb-xl">
    <h2 class="mb-md">Metrics</h2>

    <h3 class="mt-lg mb-sm">Daily Fertility Rate</h3>
    <p>
      The number of births per day per 100,000 women of childbearing age (15-44).
      This normalizes for varying month lengths and population sizes.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-lg mb-sm">Seasonality Percentage</h3>
    <p>
      The percentage of annual births occurring in each month, normalized to 30-day
      months and 360-day years. A perfectly uniform distribution would show 8.33%
      for each month.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="p-lg bg-card-bg border border-card-border rounded-lg mb-xl">
    <h2 class="mb-md">Data Sources</h2>

    <h3 class="mt-lg mb-sm">
      <a href="https://www.mortality.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">
        Human Mortality Database (HMD)
      </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Primary source for monthly births and population data. Covers 40+ countries
      with varying time ranges. Data must be manually downloaded due to license terms.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-lg mb-sm">
      <a href="https://population.un.org/wpp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">
        UN World Population Prospects
      </a>
    </h3>
    <p>
      Supplementary population data used to fill gaps where HMD data is unavailable.
      Provides estimates from 1950 to present.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-lg mb-sm">Japan Population Data</h3>
    <p>
      Historical population data from the Statistics Bureau, Ministry of Internal Affairs
      and Communications, via the fmsb R package by Minato Nakazawa.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="p-lg bg-card-bg border border-card-border rounded-lg mb-xl">
    <h2 class="mb-md">Technical Details</h2>
    <p class="mb-sm">
      Built with:
    </p>
    <ul class="ml-lg mt-sm">
      <li>Python (Polars, Pandera) for data processing</li>
      <li>Astro for static site generation</li>
      <li>D3.js for interactive visualizations</li>
      <li>Docker for containerized deployment</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="p-lg bg-card-bg border border-card-border rounded-lg">
    <h2 class="mb-md">Author</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://aaronjbecker.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-flex items-center gap-sm text-lg text-text hover:text-primary transition-colors">
        <Logo size={32} />
        <span>Aaron J Becker</span>
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
